shows.title: Stranger Things
shows.description: When a young boy vanishes, a small town uncovers a mystery involving secret experiments, terrifying supernatural forces and one strange little girl.

shows.title: Breaking Bad
shows.description: A high school chemistry teacher diagnosed with inoperable lung cancer turns to manufacturing and selling methamphetamine in order to secure his family's future.

shows.title: The Crown
shows.description: Follows the political rivalries and romance of Queen Elizabeth II's reign and the events that shaped the second half of the 20th century.

shows.title: Money Heist
shows.description: An unusual group of robbers attempt to carry out the most perfect robbery in Spanish history - stealing 2.4 billion euros from the Royal Mint of Spain.

shows.title: The Office
shows.description: A mockumentary on a group of typical office workers, where the workday consists of ego clashes, inappropriate behavior, and tedium.

shows.title: Dark
shows.description: A family saga with a supernatural twist, set in a German town, where the disappearance of two young children exposes the relationships among four families.

shows.title: Peaky Blinders
shows.description: A gangster family epic set in 1900s England, centering on a gang who sew razor blades in the peaks of their caps, and their fierce boss Tommy Shelby.

shows.title: Narcos
shows.description: A chronicled look at the criminal exploits of Colombian drug lord Pablo Escobar, as well as the many other drug kingpins who plagued the country through the years.

shows.title: The Witcher
shows.description: Geralt of Rivia, a solitary monster hunter, struggles to find his place in a world where people often prove more wicked than beasts.

shows.title: Friends
shows.description: Follows the personal and professional lives of six twenty to thirty-something-year-old friends living in Manhattan.

shows.title: Game of Thrones
shows.description: Nine noble families fight for control over the lands of Westeros, while an ancient enemy returns after being dormant for millennia.

shows.title: House of the Dragon
shows.description: The Targaryen dynasty is at the absolute apex of its power, with more than 15 dragons under their yoke. Most empires crumble from such heights. In the case of the Targaryens, their slow fall begins when King Viserys breaks with a century of tradition by naming his daughter Rhaenyra heir to the Iron Throne.

shows.title: Sherlock: The Russian Chronicles
shows.description: A modern Russian adaptation of Sir Arthur Conan Doyle's Sherlock Holmes stories, set in contemporary Russia. The brilliant detective and his loyal companion solve complex crimes using deduction and modern technology.

episodes.title: Winter Is Coming
episodes.description: Eddard Stark is torn between his family and an old friend when asked to serve at the side of King Robert Baratheon.

episodes.title: The Kingsroad
episodes.description: While Bran recovers from his fall, Ned takes only his daughters to King's Landing.

episodes.title: Lord Snow
episodes.description: Jon begins his training with the Night's Watch; Ned confronts his past and future at King's Landing.

episodes.title: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
episodes.description: Eddard investigates Jon Arryn's murder; Jon befriends Samwell Tarly, a coward who has come to join the Night's Watch.

episodes.title: The Wolf and the Lion
episodes.description: Catelyn has captured Tyrion and plans to bring him to her sister, Lysa Arryn, at the Vale, to be tried for his alleged crimes against Bran.

episodes.title: A Golden Crown
episodes.description: While recovering from his battle with Jaime, Eddard is forced to run the kingdom while Robert goes hunting.

episodes.title: You Win or You Die
episodes.description: Robert has been injured while hunting and is dying. Jon and the others finally take their vows to the Night's Watch.

episodes.title: The Pointy End
episodes.description: The Lannisters press their advantage over the Starks; Robb rallies his father's northern allies and heads south to war.

episodes.title: Baelor
episodes.description: Robb goes to war against the Lannisters. Jon finds himself struggling on deciding if his place is with Robb or the Night's Watch.

episodes.title: Fire and Blood
episodes.description: Robb vows to get revenge on the Lannisters. Jon must officially decide if his place is with Robb or the Night's Watch.

episodes.title: The North Remembers
episodes.description: As Robb Stark and his northern army continue the war against the Lannisters, Tyrion arrives in King's Landing to counsel Joffrey.

episodes.title: The Night Lands
episodes.description: Arya makes friends with Gendry. Tyrion tries to take control of the Small Council.

episodes.title: What Is Dead May Never Die
episodes.description: At the Red Keep, Tyrion plots three alliances through the promise of marriage. Catelyn arrives in the Stormlands to forge an alliance of her own.

episodes.title: Garden of Bones
episodes.description: Joffrey punishes Sansa for Robb's victories while Tyrion and Bronn scramble to temper the king's cruelty.

episodes.title: The Ghost of Harrenhal
episodes.description: The Baratheon rivalry ends; Tyrion learns of Cersei's secret weapon; Dany suffers a loss; Arya collects a debt she didn't know was owed.

episodes.title: The Old Gods and the New
episodes.description: Theon seizes control of Winterfell. Jon captures a wildling. The people of King's Landing begin to turn against King Joffrey.

episodes.title: A Man Without Honor
episodes.description: Jaime meets a distant relative. Dany receives an invitation to the House of the Undying. Theon leads a search for Bran and Rickon.

episodes.title: The Prince of Winterfell
episodes.description: Tyrion and Catelyn have both come up with a plan to save the Stark girls. Theon's plan to prove himself to his father has tragic consequences.

episodes.title: Blackwater
episodes.description: Stannis Baratheon's fleet and army arrive at King's Landing and the battle for the city begins.

episodes.title: Valar Morghulis
episodes.description: Tyrion awakens to a changed situation. King Joffrey doles out rewards to his subjects. Theon seeks a way out of Winterfell.

episodes.title: Valar Dohaeris
episodes.description: Jon meets the King-Beyond-the-Wall while his Night Watch Brothers flee south. In King's Landing, Tyrion asks for his reward.

episodes.title: Dark Wings, Dark Words
episodes.description: Sansa says too much. Shae asks Tyrion for a favor. Jaime finds a way to pass the time. Arya runs into the Brotherhood Without Banners.

episodes.title: Walk of Punishment
episodes.description: Tyrion shoulders new responsibilities. Jon is taken to the Fist of the First Men. Daenerys meets with the slavers.

episodes.title: And Now His Watch Is Ended
episodes.description: The Night's Watch takes stock. Varys meets his better. Arya is taken to the commander of the Brotherhood.

episodes.title: Kissed by Fire
episodes.description: The Hound is judged by the gods. Jaime is judged by men. Jon proves himself. Robb is betrayed.

episodes.title: The Climb
episodes.description: Tywin plans strategic unions for the Lannisters. Melisandre pays a visit to the Riverlands. Robb weighs a compromise to repair his alliance with House Frey.

episodes.title: The Bear and the Maiden Fair
episodes.description: Dany exchanges gifts with a slave lord outside of Yunkai. Jon and the Wildlings face a daunting climb.

episodes.title: Second Sons
episodes.description: King's Landing hosts a wedding, and Tyrion and Sansa spend the night together. Daenerys meets the Titan's Bastard.

episodes.title: The Rains of Castamere
episodes.description: Robb presents himself to Walder Frey, and Edmure meets his bride. Jon faces his harshest test yet.

episodes.title: Mhysa
episodes.description: Joffrey challenges Tywin. Bran tells a ghost story. In Dragonstone, mercy comes from strange quarters.

episodes.title: Two Swords
episodes.description: Tyrion welcomes a guest to King's Landing. At Castle Black, Jon Snow finds himself unwelcome.

episodes.title: The Lion and the Rose
episodes.description: A who's who of honored guests turns out for Joffrey and Margaery's wedding in King's Landing.

episodes.title: Breaker of Chains
episodes.description: Tyrion ponders his options. Tywin extends an olive branch. Sam realizes Castle Black isn't safe.

episodes.title: Oathkeeper
episodes.description: Dany balances justice and mercy. Jaime tasks Brienne with his honor. Jon secures volunteers.

episodes.title: First of His Name
episodes.description: Cersei and Tywin plan the Crown's next move. Dany discusses future plans. Jon Snow begins a new mission.

episodes.title: The Laws of Gods and Men
episodes.description: Stannis and Davos put their faith in a new strategy. Dany's sphere of influence expands.

episodes.title: Mockingbird
episodes.description: Tyrion enlists an unlikely ally. Daario entreats Dany to allow him to do what he does best.

episodes.title: The Mountain and the Viper
episodes.description: Unexpected visitors arrive in Mole's Town. Littlefinger's motives are questioned.

episodes.title: The Watchers on the Wall
episodes.description: Jon Snow and the Night's Watch face a big challenge.

episodes.title: The Children
episodes.description: Circumstances change after an unexpected arrival from north of the Wall. Dany must face harsh realities.

episodes.title: The Wars to Come
episodes.description: Cersei and Jaime adjust to a world without Tywin. Varys reveals a conspiracy to Tyrion.

episodes.title: The House of Black and White
episodes.description: Arya arrives in Braavos. Pod and Brienne run into trouble on the road. Cersei fears for her daughter's safety in Dorne.

episodes.title: High Sparrow
episodes.description: In Braavos, Arya sees the Many-Faced God. In King's Landing, Queen Margaery enjoys her new husband.

episodes.title: Sons of the Harpy
episodes.description: The Faith Militant grow increasingly aggressive. Jaime and Bronn head south. Ellaria and the Sand Snakes vow vengeance.

episodes.title: Kill the Boy
episodes.description: Dany makes a difficult decision in Meereen. Jon recruits the help of an unexpected ally. Brienne searches for Sansa.

episodes.title: Unbowed, Unbent, Unbroken
episodes.description: Arya trains. Jorah and Tyrion run into slavers. Trystane and Myrcella make plans. Jaime and Bronn reach their destination.

episodes.title: The Gift
episodes.description: Jon prepares for conflict. Sansa tries to talk to Theon. Brienne waits for a sign. Stannis remains stubborn.

episodes.title: Hardhome
episodes.description: Arya makes progress in her training. Sansa confronts an old friend. Cersei struggles. Jon travels.

episodes.title: The Dance of Dragons
episodes.description: Stannis confronts a troubling decision. Jon returns to The Wall. Mace visits the Iron Bank. Arya encounters someone from her past.

episodes.title: Mother's Mercy
episodes.description: Stannis marches. Dany is surrounded by strangers. Cersei seeks forgiveness. Jon is challenged.

episodes.title: The Red Woman
episodes.description: Jon Snow is dead. Daenerys meets a strong man. Cersei sees her daughter again.

episodes.title: Home
episodes.description: Bran trains with the Three-Eyed Raven. In King's Landing, Jaime advises Tommen. Tyrion demands good news.

episodes.title: Oathbreaker
episodes.description: Daenerys meets her future. Bran meets the past. Tommen confronts the High Sparrow. Arya trains to be No One.

episodes.title: Book of the Stranger
episodes.description: Tyrion strikes a deal. Jorah and Daario undertake a difficult task. Jaime and Cersei try to improve their situation.

episodes.title: The Door
episodes.description: Tyrion seeks a strange ally. Bran learns a great deal. Brienne goes on a mission. Arya is given a chance to prove herself.

episodes.title: Blood of My Blood
episodes.description: An old foe comes back into the picture. Gilly meets Sam's family. Arya faces a difficult choice. Jaime faces off against the High Sparrow.

episodes.title: The Broken Man
episodes.description: The High Sparrow eyes another target. Jaime confronts a hero. Arya makes a plan. The North is reminded.

episodes.title: No One
episodes.description: While Jaime weighs his options, Cersei answers a request. Tyrion's plans bear fruit. Arya faces a new test.

episodes.title: Battle of the Bastards
episodes.description: As the Starks prepare to fight, Davos loses something dear. Ramsay plays a game. Daenerys faces a choice.

episodes.title: The Winds of Winter
episodes.description: Cersei and Loras face their trial. Daenerys prepares to set sail. Jon faces the truth about his life.

episodes.title: Dragonstone
episodes.description: Jon organizes the defense of the North. Cersei tries to even the odds. Daenerys comes home.

episodes.title: Stormborn
episodes.description: Daenerys receives an unexpected visitor. Jon faces a revolt. Tyrion plans the conquest of Westeros.

episodes.title: The Queen's Justice
episodes.description: Daenerys holds court. Cersei returns a gift. Jaime learns from his mistakes.

episodes.title: The Spoils of War
episodes.description: Daenerys fights back. Jaime faces an unexpected situation. Arya comes home.

episodes.title: Eastwatch
episodes.description: Daenerys demands loyalty from the surviving Lannister soldiers. Jon heeds Bran's warning about White Walkers.

episodes.title: Beyond the Wall
episodes.description: Jon and his team go beyond the wall to capture a wight. Daenerys has to make a tough call.

episodes.title: The Dragon and the Wolf
episodes.description: Tyrion tries to save Westeros from itself. Sansa questions loyalties.

episodes.title: Winterfell
episodes.description: Jon and Daenerys arrive at Winterfell and are met with skepticism. Sam learns about the fate of his family.

episodes.title: A Knight of the Seven Kingdoms
episodes.description: Jaime argues his case before a skeptical audience. The Night King's army marches on Winterfell.

episodes.title: The Long Night
episodes.description: The Night King and his army have arrived at Winterfell and the great battle begins.

episodes.title: The Last of the Starks
episodes.description: The Battle of Winterfell is over and a new chapter begins for the survivors.

episodes.title: The Bells
episodes.description: Varys betrays his queen. Daenerys brings her forces to King's Landing.

episodes.title: The Iron Throne
episodes.description: In the aftermath of the devastating attack on King's Landing, Daenerys must face the survivors.
